INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(1,1,29,1,8.699999999999999289,90,'GK','Sweeper-keeper / last line — kept Villa level under sustained pressure (Bournemouth 20 shots, xG ~2.31 vs Villa 0.44). 7 saves (4 first-half, 3 second-half), 4 of them from inside the box; twice denied Ryan Christie late. 1.14 goals prevented, 1 punch, 3 high claims, 2 keeper-sweeper runs (1 successful). His single highest-rated match of the season and effectively man of the match.','Densest in the 6-yard box and along the goal-line, centred; secondary warmth across the full width of the penalty area (both posts) and a thin trail to the edge of the box.','Avg position pinned to his own goal-line, dead-centre laterally (SofaScore heat centroid ~x10.1/y50.9 on a 0-100 pitch). Busy, wide-covering shift: 74 heat points spread near-post to far-post (y range ~9-73) with forward activity out to the edge of the box (x range 0-41) for shot-blocking and distribution.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/emiliano-martinez/158263 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High. All three ratings, results, venues, minutes, positions, and per-match stats come directly from SofaScore''s own API','0000000000000000020001X10',49.10000000000000142,10.09999999999999965);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(2,1,18,2,8.199999999999999289,90,'GK','Sweeper-keeper anchoring a clean sheet in Villa''s first win at St James'' Park since 2005. 4 saves (all 4 from inside the box), including two crucial first-half stops from Sandro Tonali (a ~35-second ''wonder'' effort) and Lewis Miley. Highest goals-prevented of the three matches (1.31). Handled crosses aggressively — 6 high claims — and hit 39 long balls as the primary out-ball.','Hottest along the goal-line and central 6-yard box, leaning slightly to one side of goal; broad but shallow coverage across the penalty-area width (y ~31-76), little activity beyond the box.','Avg position on his own goal-line with a slight right-of-centre bias (heat centroid ~x10.4/y53.2). Most home-bound of the three (forward x range only 1-34): stayed on his line, minimal sweeping, one keeper-sweeper run. 77 heat points concentrated goal-side.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/emiliano-martinez/158263 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High. All three ratings, results, venues, minutes, positions, and per-match stats come directly from SofaScore''s own API','0000000000000000110001X00',46.79999999999999716,10.40000000000000035);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(3,1,7,3,8.199999999999999289,90,'GK','Sweeper-keeper in a dominant home win; clean sheet headlined by a one-handed penalty save from Antoine Semenyo (awarded for a Morgan Rogers handball). 3 saves (1 from inside the box) plus the spot-kick stop, 1.06 goals prevented, 2 high claims, 1 keeper-sweeper run. Comfortable on the ball in a controlled 4-0 (Buendía free-kick, Onana, Barkley, Malen).','Hottest on the goal-line and penalty-spot area (penalty-save moment), centre-left; lateral coverage y ~14-61, plus the deepest forward reach of the three into the penalty-arc zone.','Avg position on his own goal-line, marginally left-of-centre (heat centroid ~x10.5/y46.4). Came off his line furthest of the three (forward x range 0-46 — out toward the penalty spot/edge of box for the penalty save and sweeping). 63 heat points, the lowest volume, reflecting a quieter, control-oriented shift.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/emiliano-martinez/158263 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High. All three ratings, results, venues, minutes, positions, and per-match stats come directly from SofaScore''s own API','0000000000000000010000X20',53.60000000000000142,10.5);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(4,2,30,1,8.400000000000000355,90,'RB','Starting right-back in a 4-2-3-1; disciplined, defensively-anchored full-back tasked with containing City''s left-side overloads, staying compact rather than over-committing forward, but joining a set-piece routine to score. Not captain, played full 90.','Right defensive-to-middle third channel (mid|right-flank 42%, def|right-flank 38% of activity)','Average position deep-ish on the right, avg pitch coords approx (x=39, y=15) on SofaScore''s 0-100 scale — defensive-leaning for a full-back. Movement split 40% defensive third / 42% middle third / 18% attacking third; 85% of touches hugged the right touchline (y<25). Touch spread reached x=1 to x=99, i.e. he did get all the way forward once (the 19th-minute goal off Buendia''s short-corner routine, curling a low left-footed shot into the bottom corner) but his baseline was a contained, recovery-focused right-back display. 76 touches, 39/48 passing, 2 tackles, 4 clearances, 1 interception, 1 key pass, 1 big chance created, 4 duels won. Named Player of the Match.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/matty-cash/833956 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings and top-3 identification. The per-match SofaScore ratings were read directly from SofaScore''s own match ','1010100118000280001X00148',85.40000000000000569,39.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(5,2,31,2,7.900000000000000355,90,'RB','Starting right-back in a 4-2-3-1; his most attacking display of the three — pushed high and wide as Villa''s main source of right-sided width away from home, spending far more time in the opposition half than deep defending. Full 90, not captain.','Right middle third (46%) and right attacking third (32%) — camped high on the flank','Most advanced heatmap of his top matches: average position around midfield/opposition-half on the right, avg coords approx (x=54, y=14). Movement split only 18% defensive third / 46% middle third / 36% attacking third — heavily upfield. 80% of touches on the right touchline (y<25) and NONE on the far side; the y-range capped at ~47, meaning he stayed strictly on the right half of the pitch. 86 touches, 56/62 passing (high volume, high accuracy), 2 tackles, 2 clearances, 1 interception, 5 duels won. Scored Villa''s goal.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/matty-cash/833956 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings and top-3 identification. The per-match SofaScore ratings were read directly from SofaScore''s own match ','000040003X000270013500011',86.20000000000000284,54.20000000000000284);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(6,2,12,3,7.799999999999999823,87,'RB','Starting right-back in a 4-2-3-1; balanced two-way full-back display against Arsenal — high up the right when Villa attacked but with more defensive recovery work than the Sunderland game. Substituted around the 87th minute.','Right flank across all three zones, tilted to right middle third (41%) with roughly equal defensive (29%) and attacking (31%) presence','Balanced heatmap: average position around the halfway line on the right, avg coords approx (x=52, y=17). Movement split a fairly even 29% defensive third / 41% middle third / 31% attacking third — genuinely two-way. 81% of touches on the right touchline (y<25). Lower touch count (51-59 touches) reflecting a more end-to-end, transitional game and his early-ish substitution; 28/32 passing, 1 tackle, 4 clearances, 1 interception, 1 key pass, 3 duels won. Got on the scoresheet in the 2-1 win.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/player/matty-cash/833956 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings and top-3 identification. The per-match SofaScore ratings were read directly from SofaScore''s own match ','10033000170000X0002700131',82.70000000000000284,51.70000000000000284);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(10,4,1,1,7.900000000000000355,90,'LCB (left centre-back in a 4-2-3-1 back four)','Deep, defensive-anchor ball-playing centre-back. Sat very deep to protect a narrow 1-0 lead (McGinn scored; Villa''s first home goal of the season). Left-sided CB next to Konsa; job was containment and clean-sheet management rather than progression.','Own defensive third, left-centre channel (LCB zone), hugging the edge of his own penalty area; touch spread x 4-91, y 10-97 but heavily clustered deep-left.','Very deep average position: SofaScore avg coords x=26.1, y=69.1 (x: 0=own goal, 100=opp goal, so ~own third; y=69 = left-of-centre). ~70% of his 90 touch-points fell in his own third, only 3% in the attacking third. Movement was compact, mostly own-third left/left-centre channel with occasional step into the centre-half-space.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-bologna/PsKdb#id:14572679 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings, positions, and match facts; MEDIUM-QUALITATIVE on heatmaps. Ratings are pulled directly from SofaScore''','0010001100331005X12083811',30.89999999999999858,26.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(11,4,34,2,7.599999999999999645,90,'LCB (left centre-back in a 4-2-3-1 back four)','Ball-playing left centre-back / build-up initiator. Despite the defeat (Sessegnon 43''), earned his 2nd-highest rating of the season through progression and defensive reading: 88 touches, 81 passes (85.2% acc), a season-high 14 attempted long balls, 2 blocks and a last-man tackle. Stepped noticeably higher into midfield to build.','Left half-space spanning own third into the middle third; wide-left build-up positions and central circulation. Touch spread x 4-89, y 31-96.','Higher, more involved average position than Bologna: SofaScore avg coords x=35.3, y=70.5. Touch distribution split roughly own third 44% / middle third 54% / attacking third 2%, he pushed up into the middle third to receive and progress. Left-centre channel dominant (y clustered high = left side).',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/fulham-aston-villa/PsT#id:14024004 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings, positions, and match facts; MEDIUM-QUALITATIVE on heatmaps. Ratings are pulled directly from SofaScore''','00010130004X2006852043410',29.5,35.29999999999999715);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(12,4,35,3,7.5,89,'LCB (left centre-back in a 4-2-3-1 back four)','Ball-playing left centre-back in a dominant, front-foot performance that sent Villa to the Europa League final. Won the penalty for Villa''s 2nd goal (fouled by Milenkovic, VAR-reviewed, converted by Buendia 58''); also forced an early save with a header. Comfortable defensively in a clean sheet: 6 duels won, 3 aerials won, 85% passing on 40 passes. Subbed off 89'' with the tie won.','Left-centre channel from own half stepping into midfield; occasional forays into the left of the opposition box (set pieces / the won penalty). Touch spread x 6-97, y 27-97.','Attacking-minded average position for a CB: SofaScore avg coords x=37.4, y=66.7 (deeper-left but stepping up as Villa pinned Forest back). Verified as LCB by the full back-four spread that night: Cash RB y=15, Konsa RCB y=32, Torres y=67, Digne LB y=90. Touch spread reached x=97 (into the Forest box for his header/penalty-win) though the bulk stayed left-of-centre in Villa''s half.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-nottingham-forest/osP#id:15632625 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on ratings, positions, and match facts; MEDIUM-QUALITATIVE on heatmaps. Ratings are pulled directly from SofaScore''','00320200004X1002880063330',33.29999999999999715,37.39999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(13,5,24,1,8.199999999999999289,90,'LB','Attacking left-back in a 4-2-3-1; overlapping outlet on the left, supplied the assist (crossed/laid off for Buendia''s 2-0) and created a big chance while staying defensively solid in a clean sheet','Concentrated tight to the left touchline (y 63-100), stretching from own left-back slot up into the left half-space of the attacking third (x range ~11-78); hottest around the left flank between defensive and middle thirds','Average position ~45x/84y on SofaScore''s grid (deep-left, around the halfway line, hugging the left touchline); 52 touches split 21% attacking third / 40% middle / 38% defensive third — a controlled, left-sided display advancing into midfield rather than camping high',0,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/bologna-aston-villa/PsKdb#id:15632621 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High confidence on ranking, ratings, and match facts — all pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (player 96538) acros','4010045000X10005200052200',16.30000000000000071,45.20000000000000285);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(14,5,4,2,8.199999999999999289,90,'LB','Advanced left-back / auxiliary left winger in a narrow 4-2-2-2; primary crossing outlet — 7 crosses all accurate and 5 key passes, constantly overlapping and delivering into the box during the 2-1 win','Dense strip along the left touchline (y 68-98) running the full length from left-back to the by-line (x 17-88); hottest patch high on the left in the crossing/attacking zone','Average position ~51x/84y (pushed up to the halfway line and beyond on the left touchline); high 81-touch involvement split 35% attacking third / 28% middle / 37% defensive — a two-way, heavily left-flank shift with big attacking output',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-burnley/gsP#id:14025217 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High confidence on ranking, ratings, and match facts — all pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (player 96538) acros','711029100092000X400053000',16.10000000000000143,51.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(15,5,22,3,7.700000000000000177,90,'LB','High, aggressive left-back in a 4-2-3-1; the most advanced of his top displays — 8 duels won, 3 accurate crosses and heavy attacking-third presence while keeping a clean sheet','Wide left channel (y 57-97) with the deepest-to-highest spread of the three (x 9-92, tracking back to his own box and pushing all the way to the by-line); hottest concentration in the left half of the attacking third','Average position ~53x/82y (highest and busiest of the three, sitting past the halfway line on the left); a match-high 86-point touch cloud split 41% attacking third / 30% middle / 29% defensive — pinned high pressing West Ham back',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-west-ham-united/MP#id:14024014 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','High confidence on ranking, ratings, and match facts — all pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (player 96538) acros','83102X0210810008000063200',17.89999999999999857,52.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(16,6,6,1,8.300000000000000711,90,'LB (DL)','Left-back in a 4-2-3-1; overlapping/attacking full-back who linked with Rogers & Sancho and scored the opener (45''+1) with an angled finish off the underside of the crossbar. Player of the Match. Villa dominated (1.98 xG, 13 shots).','Hottest along the left flank from own half through the left half-space into the attacking third; final-third left corner lit up around his goal. 83 heat points, 68 touches, 1 key pass.','Avg position ~44/100 up the pitch (defensive base, balanced) and ~82/100 across = pinned to the LEFT touchline. Two-way left-flank coverage: recovered into own third yet pushed all the way to the opposition byline (max advancement) for his goal.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/maccabi-tel-aviv-aston-villa/PsYdc#id:14572677 (SofaScore 8.3 raw, event 14572677) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on the #1 match and on ratings/dates/results/minutes/goals/assists overall - these come straight from SofaScore''s o','1310164010X31008310093000',18.19999999999999929,44.29999999999999715);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(17,6,36,2,7.200000000000000177,73,'LB (DL)','Left-back in a 4-2-3-1 pushed high as an auxiliary left winger while Villa chased the game; most advanced of his three top games, main left-side creator (set up Rogers down the left). Subbed off on 73''. Loss came via Pau Torres/Martinez errors (Barry 59''), not Maatsen.','Hottest in the attacking-half left flank / left half-space and around the left corner of the final third; noticeably fewer defensive-third touches than usual. 70 heat points, 62 touches, 3 key passes, 1 tackle.','Avg position ~56/100 up the pitch (well into the opposition half for a full-back) and ~83/100 across = high-and-wide on the LEFT. Covered the entire left channel end-to-end (own box to opposition byline).',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/everton-aston-villa/PY#id:14025064 (SofaScore 7.2 raw, event 14025064) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on the #1 match and on ratings/dates/results/minutes/goals/assists overall - these come straight from SofaScore''s o','5200297100X2100X200030100',17.19999999999999929,55.89999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(18,6,37,3,7.200000000000000177,90,'LB (DL)','Left-back in a 4-2-3-1; highest-volume shift of the three - full 90, heavily involved in Villa''s siege of 10-man Brentford (Schade sent off 42''). Attacking overlaps plus a big defensive workload; noted out of position on Ouattara''s winner (45+2).','Hottest continuously along the left flank from the defensive third up into the attacking-third left corner; strong left half-space presence. 115 heat points (most of any match), 100 touches, 6 tackles, 3 key passes.','Avg position ~55/100 up the pitch and ~81/100 across = advanced LEFT touchline. Widest end-to-end spread of the three matches, own box (deep) to opposition byline, with the densest overall coverage.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/brentford-aston-villa/Psab#id:14025125 (SofaScore 7.2 raw, event 14025125) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on the #1 match and on ratings/dates/results/minutes/goals/assists overall - these come straight from SofaScore''s o','551006600040000X200051000',19.10000000000000143,54.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(19,8,7,1,8.199999999999999289,71,'CM (left-central of a 4-4-2 midfield, alongside Kamara; SofaScore code ''M'')','Deep-lying central midfielder / ball-winner who stepped forward into shooting range. Villa lined up 4-4-2 (Buendia, Onana, Kamara, McGinn across midfield); Onana controlled the middle, recovered balls and provided the link to attack, then arrived on the edge of the box to score.','Hottest zones central: middle-central and middle-left band ~24% each, defensive-central ~16%, attacking-central ~12%. ~53% of all activity in the central lateral band; activity length range ~x12-72 (own box up to opponent''s edge-of-area).','Average position central-midfield, roughly avgX 45 / avgY 61 on SofaScore''s 0-100 grid (own-half-leaning halfway line, offset to one central-left channel). Movement box-to-box within the central spine: 33% of touches in the defensive third, 49% in the middle third, 18% pushed into the attacking third (the highest attacking share of the three games) — reflecting the run onto Rogers'' lay-off for his 40th-minute goal.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-bournemouth/... (event 14025014); rating & heatmap via SofaScore API /event/14025014/lineups and /event/14025014/player/923973/heatmap ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH confidence on the three matches and their SofaScore ratings, which were pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (p','00100674101X9300734004630',39.10000000000000142,45.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(20,8,30,2,8.099999999999999645,90,'CM/DM (central midfield, deeper of the pair; SofaScore code ''M'')','Defensive midfield anchor in Villa''s disciplined game plan that stifled City. Screened the back four, won midfield duels and famously blocked a Foden shot with his face. Very few forward incursions - a pure holding/ball-winning shift. Passing kept simple and near-flawless (42/43, 4/4 long balls).','Hottest zone defensive-central ~30%, then middle-central ~23%, middle-left ~16%, defensive-left ~13%. ~60% of activity in the central band - the most central/compact heat of the three matches.','Deepest of the three games: average position avgX ~38 / avgY ~56 (clearly own-half, sitting in front of the defence). Movement compressed and deep: 46% defensive third, 46% middle third, only ~9% attacking third. Length range ~x7-64 - rarely crossed into the final third, reflecting the containment role against City.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-manchester-city/... (event 14025257); rating & heatmap via SofaScore API /event/14025257/lineups and /event/14025257/player/923973/heatmap ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH confidence on the three matches and their SofaScore ratings, which were pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (p','0110015230065114552011X20',43.70000000000000285,38.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(21,8,22,3,7.900000000000000355,90,'CM/DM in a double pivot (Villa 4-2-3-1; SofaScore code ''M'')','All-action central midfielder in a two-man pivot - the most ball-winning display of the three: 7 tackles, 3 interceptions, 5 recoveries, 8/13 duels won, 1 block, plus 2 shots (xG 0.17) and a key pass. Dominated the middle third defensively and progressively.','Concentrated in the central and central-flank channels around the halfway line; ~50%+ central band with heavy middle-third density (the 59% middle-third share is the largest of the three matches). Length range roughly x mid-teens to ~70.','Confirmed by SofaScore average-position data: avgX ~47.4 / avgY ~44.1 (right around the halfway line, central). Highest work-rate footprint of the three (83 recorded heat points). Movement spread across the middle: 27% defensive third, 59% middle third, 14% attacking third - a mid-block, box-to-box central profile.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-west-ham-united/... (event 14024014); rating, heatmap & average-position via SofaScore API /event/14024014/lineups, /player/923973/heatmap, /average-positions ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH confidence on the three matches and their SofaScore ratings, which were pulled directly from SofaScore''s own API (p','004100266X1X8733849102610',56.39999999999999858,47.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(25,10,35,1,8.699999999999999289,89,'RM / right-of-midfield-four (RCM)','Right-sided box-to-box 8 in a 4-2-3-1; all-action pressing high up, then late arriving runs into the box. Both goals came from cutbacks/driven passes finished into the low corners (77'' Watkins assist, 80'' Rogers assist) — first Villa player to score a brace in a major European semi. Withdrawn on 89'' for Bailey.','Right half-space and right-central attacking third; edge of the penalty area (both finishes) plus right-flank pressing zones','Average position on the right-centre of Villa''s midfield, pushed high toward the Forest box in the second half; heavy right-half-space and right-channel involvement with repeated late runs to the edge/inside of the penalty area where both goals were scored.',2,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-4-0-nottingham-forest-buendia-lights-europa-league ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM','001270023X000390010500002',85.09999999999999431,62.89999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(26,10,41,2,8.5,90,'RM / right-of-midfield-four (RCM)','Right-sided central midfielder / box-to-box in a 4-2-3-1; Player of the Match (Sky 9/10, PotM). First PL brace of his Villa career — 49'' left-footed finish into the far corner from Matty Cash''s right-wing cutback, then 73'' ran onto a Tielemans long ball, rounded the keeper and finished into an empty net from distance. Set the tempo with his usual high work rate.','Right half-space / right channel into the attacking third; central edge-of-box and inside-right penalty-area pockets (both goals)','Average position right-central midfield, shuttling forward into the right side of the Forest box; strongest presence in the right half-space and central attacking third, with a deeper right-flank base when Villa were out of possession.',2,0,'https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4516483/astonvilla-3-nottinghamforest-1-match-report-3-january-2026 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM | rating corrected 8.6→8.5 to SofaScore API official (2026-07-02).','0014X00269103541022200010',76.70000000000000284,66.40000000000000569);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(27,10,27,NULL,7.599999999999999645,90,'RM / right-of-midfield-four (RCM)','Captain, right side of the midfield four in a 4-2-3-1; steady, controlling display with an assist (fed Buendia to curl in the second) and 3 key passes as Villa cruised to the trophy. More measured/possession-based than the Forest games, cutting inside from the right to link play.','Right-central middle third and right half-space (build-up/link zones); assist created from the right side into the box','Average position on the right of central midfield in a neutral-venue final; balanced right-half-space footprint with fewer penalty-box arrivals than the Forest matches — activity skewed to right-central middle third and progressive passing zones.',0,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-win-europa-league-as-emery-lifts-his-fifth-title ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM','0224X3107X021660113700000',72.0,64.20000000000000284);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(28,11,42,1,7.299999999999999823,83,'CDM (DM)','Deep-lying defensive midfielder in one of the two pivot slots of Emery''s 4-2-3-1. Screening job: sat in front of the back four, helped track Grealish (McGinn/Bogarde/Cash all dropped onto him), broke up play and recycled possession simply. Season-high SofaScore rating.','Own defensive third and deep central midfield (the ''6'' zone), slightly favouring the right-centre channel; sparse in the final third.','Average position deep and just right-of-central in the defensive/deep-mid zone (heatmap centroid approx x=35, y=46 on SofaScore''s 0-100 grid, 0=own goal). Distribution: ~50% of activity in the defensive third, ~36% middle third, only ~14% in the attacking third. Movement laterally balanced (right ~36% / central ~38% / left ~26%) with occasional pushes as high as x=78 but a clear deep, box-to-touchline defensive footprint.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/everton-aston-villa/OstPT#id:14025136 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)',unistr('MODERATE-HIGH on ratings/positions, QUALITATIVE on heatmaps.\u000a\u000aDATA SOURCE: Ratings, minutes, positions, and heatmap coor'),'00000181050441116596118X0',54.29999999999999716,35.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(29,11,7,2,7.200000000000000177,9,'CDM (DM)','Late substitute cameo (~9 min) in the pivot to see out a 4-0 win. Small sample: 12 touches, won a couple of duels/tackles, tidy on the ball. High rating relative to tiny minutes — CAVEAT: this is a brief cameo, not a full performance, so heatmap/movement read is very limited. If you want three FULL-match performances, substitute the Basel match (also 7.2, 90 min) below in its place.','Deep central-right midfield / edge of own third only; negligible final-third presence.','Only ~13 heatmap touch-points over 9 minutes. Centroid deep and central-to-right (approx x=34, y=41). ~54% defensive third / ~38% middle third / ~8% attacking third. Too small a sample for a meaningful movement pattern — essentially a deep holding cameo shielding the lead.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-bournemouth/tsPT#id:14025014 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)',unistr('MODERATE-HIGH on ratings/positions, QUALITATIVE on heatmaps.\u000a\u000aDATA SOURCE: Ratings, minutes, positions, and heatmap coor'),'000000030033007033X300070',59.5,33.5);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(30,11,13,3,7.200000000000000177,90,'CDM (DM)','Full 90 as the deep pivot in a heavily-rotated Villa XI (Emery made 8 changes; league-phase win no. 8). Metronome role: 61 passes / 56 accurate (~92%), 82 touches, 8 ball recoveries, 3 interceptions, 4 tackles, 23 ball carries. Anchored midfield through the win. Most substantial of his top-rated performances.','Right-of-centre deep and middle third (right half-space of the pivot); very little left-side or final-third activity.','Average position in the deep/central-midfield band pulled markedly to one side: centroid approx x=40, y=24 on SofaScore''s grid, i.e. right-of-centre. Distribution ~38% defensive third / ~55% middle third / ~7% attacking third, and strongly lateralised (~72% toward the right side, ~27% central, ~1% left). Reached as high as x=93 once but the mass sits deep-right — a right-sided holding pivot who shuttled between his own third and centre circle.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/basel-aston-villa/pMbsIdb#id:14572748 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)',unistr('MODERATE-HIGH on ratings/positions, QUALITATIVE on heatmaps.\u000a\u000aDATA SOURCE: Ratings, minutes, positions, and heatmap coor'),'000000000500358012X800113',75.70000000000000284,39.5);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(31,12,5,1,7.799999999999999823,90,'CDM (left pivot in a 4-2-3-1 double pivot)','Deep-lying holding midfielder / ball-winner. A defensively dominant, disruptive display screening the back four in Villa''s away win. Statline: 41/46 passes (89%), 14 of 17 duels won, 4 tackles, 2 clearances, 5 ball recoveries, drew 4 fouls, 0 times dispossessed. Low on the ball (61 touches, 3 long balls) — this was a defense-first, screen-and-recycle performance rather than a creative one.','Hottest zones: central middle-third (24%) and left half of the defensive third (23%), then left-of-center midfield (16%). Split ~49% left / 41% center / 11% right; ~38% defensive / 47% middle / 15% attacking third.','Average position sits just left of center in the middle third (SofaScore coords ~x43/y36). Movement was compact and disciplined — he ranged from his own box (x-min 8) up to the edge of the final third but spent little time high (only ~15% of activity in the attacking third). Strong left-of-center lean, minimal right-flank involvement.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-tottenham-hotspur/osZ (SofaScore event 14025249) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on core facts, medium on exact ranking order due to ties | LANE CORRECTION 2026-07-02: the left/right labels in heat_zones/heat_summary of this row are INVERTED relative to the verified SofaScore convention (y low = right; Cash RB y~15, Digne LB y~89). The raw centroids (y~36-37) are correct and mean RIGHT-of-centre. Season average-positions confirm: 26 matches, mean y=42.6, 12 right / 12 centre / 2 left (player_match_positions player_id=12).','0000203425035X21177200064',64.0,43.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(32,12,10,2,7.799999999999999823,88,'CDM (left pivot in a 4-2-3-1 double pivot)','Holding midfielder who stepped forward to decide the derby: scored the 67th-minute winner, a ~20-yard strike into the top corner (Sky Sports Man of the Match). More progressive on the ball than usual for a pivot — 50/59 passes (85%), 32/37 in the opposition half, 71 touches. Defensive contribution lighter than his best games (2 tackles, 1 recovery, duels split 7 won/8 lost).','Hottest zones: left-of-center midfield (33%) and central midfield (27%), with pockets in the attacking third (center 9%, left 9%). Split ~48% left / 43% center / 9% right; ~16% defensive / 66% middle / 18% attacking third.','Average position advanced to roughly the halfway line (SofaScore coords ~x52/y36), reflecting a more forward, box-arriving role. Ranged from own third up to the Wolves box (x-max 94); ~66% of his activity was in the middle third with pushes into the left half-space where his shot originated.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-wolverhampton/dsZ (SofaScore event 14025093) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on core facts, medium on exact ranking order due to ties | LANE CORRECTION 2026-07-02: the left/right labels in heat_zones/heat_summary of this row are INVERTED relative to the verified SofaScore convention (y low = right; Cash RB y~15, Digne LB y~89). The raw centroids (y~36-37) are correct and mean RIGHT-of-centre. Season average-positions confirm: 26 matches, mean y=42.6, 12 right / 12 centre / 2 left (player_match_positions player_id=12).','0010102383001X20343200010',64.5,52.5);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(33,12,41,3,7.700000000000000177,90,'CDM (left pivot / deep controller in a 4-2-3-1)','Deep-lying playmaking anchor — his highest-volume game of the run: 114 touches, 86/93 passes (92%, incl. 5/5 long balls and 59/66 in the opposition half), 1 key pass. Also his best defensive combined output: 6 tackles, 4 interceptions, 6 ball recoveries, 4 aerials won, 14 duels won. Dictated tempo from the base of midfield in a comfortable home win. Tied on rating (7.7) with the Newcastle home draw (16 Aug), but a clearly stronger underlying performance.','Hottest zones: left-of-center midfield (28%) and central midfield (19%), with a notably hot left attacking-third pocket (17%) and some right-side switch play (10%). Split ~52% left / 34% center / 14% right; ~13% defensive / 57% middle / 30% attacking third.','Average position just past halfway on the left of center (SofaScore coords ~x54/y37) with the widest spread of the three — active from deep (x-min 11) to the Forest box (x-max 91) and touching both flanks (y 3–94). ~30% of activity in the attacking third shows how high and involved he was as the controlling pivot.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-nottingham-forest/osP (SofaScore event 14025276) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','HIGH on core facts, medium on exact ranking order due to ties | LANE CORRECTION 2026-07-02: the left/right labels in heat_zones/heat_summary of this row are INVERTED relative to the verified SofaScore convention (y low = right; Cash RB y~15, Digne LB y~89). The raw centroids (y~36-37) are correct and mean RIGHT-of-centre. Season average-positions confirm: 26 matches, mean y=42.6, 12 right / 12 centre / 2 left (player_match_positions player_id=12).','00201043X6045840054200011',63.0,54.39999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(34,13,14,1,9.30000000000000072,90,'AML / inside-left forward (left of the 3 behind Watkins in 4-2-3-1)','Inside forward / left-sided creator: starts wide left, drifts into the left half-space and central zones onto his right foot; late arrivals into the box plus long-range shooting.','Left half-space, left channel, edge-of-box central shooting zone; high up the pitch','Average position advanced and left-of-centre in the attacking half; touch density in the left half-space with drives into central/inside-left shooting zones. Comeback brace: took a Tielemans cross to slam in the 2-2 equaliser (50''), then a swerving 25-yard strike into the top corner (79''). Qualitative read (SofaScore per-match heatmap is an image, not directly extractable).',2,0,'https://www.flashscore.com/news/soccer-premier-league-rogers-scores-sensational-brace-as-aston-villa-produce-comeback-win-at-west-ham/lvW5hGQQ/ ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM-HIGH on match SELECTION and factual details (dates, results, goals/assists, positions, roles cross-checked across | rating corrected 8.84→9.3 to SofaScore API official (2026-07-02).','73210X4101530107000020100',20.60000000000000143,62.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(35,13,26,NULL,8.300000000000000711,90,'AMC (No.10 in 4-2-3-1)','Advanced central creator and progressive carrier: safe circulation then risk in advanced areas; 10 carries (6 progressive, 148m advanced) set up his chance creation. Goal from a Digne cutback (42'') plus an assist.','Central attacking third and left half-space; box entries via cutbacks/carries','Average position high and central/left in the final third; touch clusters in central-to-left attacking zones with box entries. 31 passes (21 acc.), 4 key passes, 2 big chances created, 6 recoveries, 10 carries (6 progressive, best 35m). SofaScore 8.3 confirmed as Villa''s top-rated player. Heat read qualitative (heatmap is an image).',1,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/morgan-rogers-delivers-in-aston-villa-4-2-liverpool-win ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02) ; [2026-07-02 merged: duplicate matches row 43 (2026-05-16) folded into 26 (2026-05-15, API date)]','MEDIUM-HIGH on match SELECTION and factual details (dates, results, goals/assists, positions, roles cross-checked across','321422824X001411020100152',59.5,61.29999999999999716);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(36,13,15,3,8.699999999999999289,90,'AML / left forward drifting inside (left of the 3 in 4-2-3-1)','Inside forward off the left: drifts inside off the left flank onto his right foot to shoot; two curled strikes from the inside-left channel. Also stretched the back line to create space. Season-high 7 shots.','Left flank and inside-left channel curling into central edge-of-box zones','Average position left-of-centre and advanced; activity concentrated on the left flank and inside-left channel, repeatedly drifting infield into central shooting positions. Both goals curled from the inside-left area (one before HT past Yoro, one ~58''). Man-of-the-match; SofaScore Team of the Week. Heat read qualitative (heatmap is an image).',2,0,'https://onefootball.com/en/news/player-ratings-morgan-rogers-shines-as-aston-villa-beat-man-united-42128581 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM-HIGH on match SELECTION and factual details (dates, results, goals/assists, positions, roles cross-checked across | rating corrected 8.46→8.7 to SofaScore API official (2026-07-02).','034111143061030X600077300',32.0,45.20000000000000285);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(37,15,21,1,7.5,84,'RW (right wing, inverted)','Inverted right winger drifting infield; provided width in build-up then cut central to create. Assisted John McGinn''s opener (latched onto an Emi Martinez long ball, drove into the box dragging defenders wide, cut it back for McGinn). Also hit the woodwork late. Widely called his best display in a Villa shirt (McGinn: MOTM ''by a mile''); OneFootball 7.5.','Densest cluster in the attacking third on the right flank (x 70-95, right channel), secondary cluster centrally in the middle third as he cut infield; touches spanned full pitch width (y 0-100), reaching the byline (x max 95).','Average position advanced and right-sided, approx x 62 / y 28 (opponent half, right channel). Heaviest touches in the attacking third; active 84 minutes with high ball-carrying volume (24 carries, 7 progressive).',0,1,'https://api.sofascore.com/api/v1/event/15631843/player/851100/statistics ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM-HIGH on the identity of the top-3 matches and the SofaScore ratings; MEDIUM on heatmap specifics. Ratings are pul','510540025X000061024601010',72.59999999999999431,60.70000000000000284);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(38,15,17,2,7.400000000000000355,75,'RW (right wing, inverted)','Wide forward on the right who got into central goal-scoring positions. Scored the only goal — a 25th-minute header at the near/six-yard area from Matty Cash''s deflected cross — his first Villa goal, sealing last-16 progression. Named Flashscore Man of the Match. Wasteful otherwise (2 big chances missed, 4 shots, xG 1.06); subbed off 75''.','Hottest zone right flank in the attacking third right up to the byline (x 86-98); secondary central cluster in the middle third; a deeper cluster in his own half showing defensive contribution. Wide x-span (4-98).','Average position around x 55 / y 31 (halfway line, right-of-centre). Asymmetric: advanced right-flank presence in attack (x 86-98) plus deeper defensive tracking, some of it toward the left, reflecting his off-ball work.',1,0,'https://api.sofascore.com/api/v1/event/14572701/player/851100/statistics ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM-HIGH on the identity of the top-3 matches and the SofaScore ratings; MEDIUM on heatmap specifics. Ratings are pul','005242012X012430134100133',70.90000000000000569,54.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(39,15,22,3,7.099999999999999645,67,'RW (right wing, inverted)','Right winger; 1 assist and 1 big chance created (3 key passes), 22/26 passes with 21 accurate in the opposition half — a high-quality creative outing feeding John McGinn / Ollie Watkins in Villa''s 2-0 win. Subbed at 67''. SofaScore 7.1 (alt fluid rating 7.3); FotMob 7.7 (his top FotMob score of the season), WhoScored 7.11.','Primary hot zone attacking third, central-to-right (x 75-95, y 0-35) close to the opponent goal; secondary central middle-third cluster (x 60-75); only token defensive-third touches. Reached the byline (x max 99).','Most advanced average position of the three, approx x 74 / y 27 — pinned high and right in the opposition half. Touches concentrated near the opponent box; limited defensive involvement.',0,1,'https://api.sofascore.com/api/v1/event/14024014/player/851100/statistics ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM-HIGH on the identity of the top-3 matches and the SofaScore ratings; MEDIUM on heatmap specifics. Ratings are pul','011453133X000020002000010',71.79999999999999716,72.29999999999999716);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(40,16,25,1,8.699999999999999289,90,'ST','Lone centre-forward in a 4-2-3-1; classic penalty-box striker on the day - two headed goals attacking crosses, then dropped to turn provider for Rogers. Highest SofaScore rating of his 2025/26 season.','Central penalty area / six-yard box (hottest); attacking-half central zone; brief drop to top of the box for the assist','Very high, central average position as the lone ST; heat pinned to the central penalty area / six-yard box (both goals were headers from wide deliveries at ~2'' and 36''), with a secondary touch dropping to the edge of the box to set up Rogers at 47''. Minimal wide drifting this match - almost pure central box occupation.',2,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-4-3-sunderland-abraham-wins-it-at-the-death ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM','07X3208230373005300000200',37.20000000000000285,65.40000000000000569);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(41,16,26,2,8.199999999999999289,90,'ST','Lone striker in the 4-2-3-1 behind/alongside Morgan Rogers; focal point in transition. Quiet, hold-up-heavy first half, then decisive after the break (goals 57'' and 73'') and turned provider for McGinn late. Rogers edged him for the match''s top Villa rating (8.3).','Central penalty area (hottest); left half-space / left channel link with Rogers; attacking-third central band','High and central average position; heat concentrated in the central penalty area (both goals close-range finishes off a Rogers set-up and a rebound from Pau Torres'' shot) with a left-of-centre channel link-up with Rogers, plus a late touch supplying McGinn. Occupied the Liverpool box in the second-half surge.',2,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-4-2-liverpool-watkins-brace-rogers-stars ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM','17X1410463103001300010100',47.60000000000000142,71.70000000000000284);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(42,16,28,3,8.5,90,'ST','Lead striker in a defensive, counter-attacking Villa setup (8 changes, effectively a front two with Barkley out of possession) on the PL final day at the Etihad; widely named man of the match. Equalised 30s after the restart and won it with an individual counter (sat Stones down, finished past Trafford). Rating is my estimate - exact SofaScore number not cleanly sourced.','Central attacking zone / penalty spot on the two finishes; right-of-centre channel and transition lanes from midfield into the box on counters','Lower, deeper average position than his home braces because of the away/counter-attacking brief - heat sits in transitional zones running from the halfway line into the box rather than sustained box occupation. Central-to-right channel bursts in behind on the break; less involvement in first-half build-up, activity spiking in the second half around both goals.',2,0,'https://cityxtra.co.uk/47089/match-report-and-player-ratings-manchester-city-1-2-aston-villa-premier-league/ ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','MEDIUM','82X3030022533022322000200',38.5,66.29999999999999716);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(43,13,30,NULL,7.5,90,'Left of the front three / left-sided 10 in the 4-2-3-1; drops to left-midfield in the defensive block','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Average position left half-space/left-inside-forward channel, advanced when Villa had the ball. Hottest zones: left half-space and left flank in the attacking and middle thirds, plus deeper touches on the left as he tracked back. Movement: two-way — carried and combined on the left in transition (Villa''s main out-ball down the left), then dropped to fill the left of a bank of four out of possession so the 4-2-3-1 read as a 4-4-2/4-4-1-1 mid-block. Modest attacking output this game (WhoScored/media rating ~6), so his heatmap is more work-rate/coverage than final-third penetration. Confidence moderate — inferred from tactical reports + role, not a pixel read of the image.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis ; SofaScore API /event/14025257/player/948261 heatmap+statistics (2026-07-02); 48 heat points, 39 touches','Moderate overall, and explicitly QUALITATIVE. Per-match heatmaps on SofaScore and Fotmob are rendered as images, so I co | grid/rating HIGH — measured from SofaScore API (그리드 세분화 샘플).','113200104213220066X003040',52.79999999999999716,45.79999999999999715);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(44,12,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right-sided pivot of the double six alongside Onana','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Average position deep-central, in front of the back four. Hottest zones: central channel in the middle third; frequently drops to the base/between or just ahead of the center-backs. In the mid-block Villa''s shape became a 5-4-1 at times with Kamara dropping into the backline for ''extra solidarity'' (per Total Football Analysis). In build-up he formed passing triangles with the CBs and full-backs and occasionally carried into the wide/right channel. So his heatmap is compact and central with a deep bias, spilling right and toward the back line. Rated ~7. Confidence moderate-high — corroborated by two tactical sources.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Moderate overall, and explicitly QUALITATIVE. Per-match heatmaps on SofaScore and Fotmob are rendered as images, so I co',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(45,16,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lone striker (tip of the 4-2-3-1), until subbed 86'' for Malen','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Average position high and central, the most advanced Villa player. Hottest zones: central channel in the attacking third and around the edge/inside of the City box; runs onto the shoulder of the last defender. Movement: repeated in-behind runs on defenders'' blindsides to exploit City''s high line in transition — Villa''s chief counter threat; came ''inches away'' from a through-ball and had a header blocked. Lower defensive footprint (front of a mid-block, minimal tracking). Heatmap = a high, narrow central hot spot with vertical run trails toward goal. Confidence moderate.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Moderate overall, and explicitly QUALITATIVE. Per-match heatmaps on SofaScore and Fotmob are rendered as images, so I co',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(46,10,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right of the midfield/attacking band (right winger/right-8) until subbed 74'' for Barkley','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Average position right side, but with a lower/deeper bias than a pure winger. Hottest zones: right half-space and right flank across the middle and attacking thirds, plus deeper right-midfield territory when he dropped in. Movement: makes runs from deep to start and join moves, then tucks into the right of the bank of four out of possession (the wide man dropping is what turns the 4-2-3-1 into a 4-4-2/4-4-1-1). Genuine goal threat — a shot deflected off Stones just wide and a blocked header from a corner; a McGinn effort was blocked by Dias. Rated ~7. So a busy two-way right-side heatmap. Confidence moderate.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Moderate overall, and explicitly QUALITATIVE. Per-match heatmaps on SofaScore and Fotmob are rendered as images, so I co',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(47,13,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Left of the front three (LW/inside-left No.10 hybrid), 4-2-3-1','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: nominal left-attack but roamed heavily and drifted infield/central, consistent with his season pattern (PL tactical piece: he ''drops deep, runs in behind, finds pockets between the lines, pulls out wide''). Hottest zones read as left half-space and centre between Brighton''s lines rather than hugging the touchline. Movement: key creative spark — provided the ''searching pass'' from a central/left pocket for Watkins'' 2nd (45+7''), so his influence peaks arriving into the left half-space to feed the channel behind Brighton''s line. Downside noted: lost possession ~20 times, i.e. lots of high-volume touches in congested central zones. Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(48,12,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deeper of the double pivot (holding No.6)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: lowest and most central of the midfield, hottest zone just ahead of the back four in central/left-central areas. Sat as the anchor (''a solid shield in front of the back four'') while Onana advanced — effectively the lone screen when both FBs pushed on. Movement: minimal vertical roaming; tidy, possession-recycling role, kept the ball moving before being subbed. Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(49,16,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Centre-forward (lone striker)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: central and high, but hot zones skew to channel/shoulder runs off the last man rather than static centre. Both goals came from movement into space — 37'' sliding to finish Maatsen''s low left cross (arriving at the near/left of the six-yard area), 45+7'' running onto Rogers'' through-ball into the channel behind Brighton''s line. MOTM (rated ~9–9.5). Movement: constant diagonal running across both centre-backs, pinning then darting behind; strong link play. Confidence: MEDIUM-HIGH (movement corroborated by goal builds).',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(50,10,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Central attacking midfielder (No.10) — captain','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: nominal central 10 but had an uncharacteristically quiet, low-influence game (''anonymous'', ''struggled to get into the game'', rated ~5.5); picked up a needless yellow. Expected heat is central just behind Watkins, but he registered few standout touches, so his footprint was muted/central-to-slightly-deep. When Villa protected the lead he pushed up toward Watkins as the second man in a 4-4-2 press. Confidence: MEDIUM on role, higher that his output/footprint was limited.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(51,8,11,NULL,7.299999999999999823,90,'Advanced/box-to-box side of the double pivot','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: paired Kamara but given freedom to surge forward — hot zones stretch from central midfield into both boxes. Scored the 60'' header (arrived at the back post on Cash''s inswinger, out-jumping De Cuyper) and hit the woodwork; won ~7 duels, ~5 tackles. Movement: the key vertical runner from midfield, physically dominant end-to-end. Confidence: MEDIUM-HIGH (corroborated by goal + duel stats).',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis ; SofaScore API /event/14025129/player/923973 heatmap (2026-07-02); 65 heat points','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor | grid HIGH — measured (표본 보강 2026-07-02).','01110111103X2203741021110',36.0,42.20000000000000285);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(52,6,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Left-back (very attacking)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: pushed high and wide on the left — one of Villa''s widest, most advanced average positions on that flank. Provided the assist for Watkins'' 1st (beat Wieffer down the left, low centre). Movement: repeated overlapping/underlapping runs, ''constant desire to get forward'', primary left-side width source since Rogers tucked in. Confidence: MEDIUM-HIGH (assist + reports).',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(53,2,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right-back (attacking, crossing outlet)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: advanced on the right, hottest as a wide/crossing outlet and set-piece deliverer more than a byline overlap — supplied the inswinging corner for Onana''s header and an assist, but was part of a defensively loose right side early. High-energy, up-and-down footprint. Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(54,18,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right of the front three (RW)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: nominal right-attack but ''often drifted to the periphery'' — lower-volume, intermittent footprint; still contributed an assist but also missed a big chance. Right/right-half-space zones, less central involvement than Rogers on the left. Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(55,3,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right centre-back','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: right-central defensive third; ''the calmer of the two centre-backs'', made key interventions and stood up to late Brighton pressure; header hit the woodwork (so pushed up for an attacking set piece). Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(56,4,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Left centre-back','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: left-central defensive third; poor first half — ''calamitous'' own goal (29'') amid early chaos, settled later but rated worst (~4.5). Footprint left-central, slightly higher when building from the back. Confidence: MEDIUM.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(57,9,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Central midfield (substitute, game-management)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'This match: came off the bench to help see the game out with composure in central midfield as Villa shifted to a more compact 4-4-2/4-1-4-1 block; limited, deep-central footprint. Confidence: MEDIUM-LOW (sub minutes only).',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MEDIUM overall. Confirmed with high confidence: the 4-2-3-1 lineup and each player''s nominal position (FotMob + Sky Spor',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(58,13,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Left of the attacking three (nominal LW/LM in 4-2-3-1)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Team-high 75 tracked touch-points and 56 total touches. SofaScore avg position X=56, Y=63 — advanced and left-of-centre, but NOT hugging the touchline. Hottest zones: left half-space and central left channel in the attacking half, plus a clear cold-defensive smear from tracking back. Movement: heavily inverting — repeatedly tucked inside off the left to ''support the double pivot in building through the centre'' and to contest Martínez''s longer goal-kicks. In the late-game defensive phase (after Arsenal''s subs) he recovered very deep, ''almost acting as a second full-back'' on Villa''s 5-3-2/5-4-1 block. His 29'' left-side cross reached the back post for Cash''s blocked shot. High duel volume (15 won / 11 lost) reflects a busy two-way, transition-heavy game rather than a touchline chalk-hugger.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MODERATE-TO-GOOD, mixed-basis read. STRONG on lineup/formation and on the quantitative average positions and per-player ',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(59,12,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deeper/right of the double pivot (No. 6)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Team-high 76 tracked points and 60 touches with excellent 42/46 passing. Avg position X=50, Y=36 — the true anchor: deepest of the outfield midfielders, sat slightly right of centre in front of the back line (roughly ahead of Konsa). Hottest zone: central-to-right defensive third and halfway line. Movement: the low-mobility screen — held position to shield the space Zubimendi/Ødegaard/Rice attacked, tidied second balls, and recycled possession to beat the press. 4 tackles won + 1 interception; the least vertical of Villa''s midfield trio, providing the base that let Tielemans push up and the fullbacks fly forward.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MODERATE-TO-GOOD, mixed-basis read. STRONG on lineup/formation and on the quantitative average positions and per-player ',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(60,16,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Central striker (tip of the 4-2-3-1)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'Only 31 touches / 6-of-13 passing — a low-volume, high-threat night typical of leading a compact counter-attacking side vs a possession team. Avg position X=55, Y=61 — modest X for a striker (confirms he repeatedly dropped) and a slight drift to the left channel. Hottest zones: centrally around Arsenal''s defensive line, with a secondary pocket dropping toward the ball. Movement: the described dual role — ''dropped to engage on first contact but also on the shoulder, ready for flick-ons'' off Martínez''s long distribution, giving Villa a two-stage aerial/transition outlet. Best chance early: released by McGinn, beat Timber and White before Raya''s fine save; also tested Raya with a low shot later. 4 duels won / 4 lost.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MODERATE-TO-GOOD, mixed-basis read. STRONG on lineup/formation and on the quantitative average positions and per-player ',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(61,10,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right of the attacking three (nominal RM/RW in 4-2-3-1)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'30 touches, 14/19 passing across 39 tracked points. Avg position X=55, Y=24 — advanced and clearly on the RIGHT (mirror image of Rogers on the left), i.e. he started the right-sided wide-mid role, not central midfield. Hottest zones: right half-space / right channel in the middle-to-attacking third, ahead of and outside Cash''s underlap. Movement: like Rogers he inverted to contest long balls and support the pivot centrally, then formed the right side of Villa''s 4-4-2 defensive block. Provided the killer early pass to spring Watkins. High duels-lost count (3 won / 7 lost) reflects a physically committed, transition-heavy shift screening Arsenal''s left.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MODERATE-TO-GOOD, mixed-basis read. STRONG on lineup/formation and on the quantitative average positions and per-player ',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(62,9,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No. 10 / free central attacking midfielder','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'52 touches, 28/35 passing, 61 tracked points. Avg position X=53, Y=47 — dead-central and slightly the most balanced of the trio, sitting between Arsenal''s midfield and defensive lines. Hottest zone: central ''zone 14'' pocket between the lines. Movement: the connector who ''found clever spaces between the lines,'' dropping to receive between Zubimendi and the Arsenal back line and stepping up into the half-spaces the fullbacks vacated. Man-marked by Zubimendi in Arsenal''s press, which is why his touch count is moderate; his job was to occupy and pin the pivot so Kamara/Onana could progress.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','MODERATE-TO-GOOD, mixed-basis read. STRONG on lineup/formation and on the quantitative average positions and per-player ',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(63,12,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right-sided defensive midfielder of the double pivot (with Onana), 4-2-3-1','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. Deepest of the outfielders alongside Onana — hot zone is the central band just ahead of the CBs (Konsa/Lindelöf), forming the base that let Tielemans, McGinn and Rogers push on. Anchored the middle; positionally disciplined rather than a runner. MOVEMENT: minimal vertical roaming — stays central to screen and recycle. As West Ham (4-3-1-2) attacked centrally through Paquetá/Fernandes early, Kamara''s zone tightens centrally in the first half; in the dominant second half his average position edges higher as Villa camp in the WH half. Note: after Onana was subbed at 64'', Kamara covered more of the central pivot space alone alongside the incoming shape.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(64,16,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lone striker (ST), 4-2-3-1 — subbed 75'' (Buendía); rated modestly','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. Highest and most central average position of any Villa player, pinned to the West Ham centre-backs (Mavropanos/Todibo) around the top of the box and penalty spot. Hot zone is central, in and around the D. MOVEMENT: classic centre-forward occupation — cross-and-near-post runs plus dropping to link. His run across Mavropanos on McGinn''s 9th-min cross forced the own goal (he made the run without being credited). Tightly marked early so touches were limited; a fixed reference point stretching the WH line rather than a wide/roaming forward. Off at 75'' for Buendía with Villa in control.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(65,10,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right of the attacking three (right-sided No.10 / right midfield), captain, 4-2-3-1 — rated ~7','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. Started right of the front line but with typical McGinn box-to-box roaming — hot zones on the right half-space/right channel plus deeper central touches. Assisted the 9th-min own goal with a ''teasing'' cross from the right, and played passes in behind for Rogers and (later) Malen. MOVEMENT: shuttles between the right flank (overlapping/underlapping with Cash) and central areas; also noted pressing at the back post. His side (right) was Villa''s crossing/service side while the left (Rogers/Maatsen) was the primary progression channel targeting the space behind Wan-Bissaka.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(66,9,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Central attacking midfielder (the No.10), 4-2-3-1 — ''Villa''s most creative player'', rated 8','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. Started centrally as the 10 but with wide licence — the assist for the 2-2 came from a ''lung-busting run down the right''/whipped cross after West Ham (Paquetá) gave the ball away, so his heat shows a central base with a strong right-side/right half-space spike into the final third. Described as thriving in the 10 role and Villa''s chief creator. MOVEMENT: central-to-right drift, arriving late into the right channel and the box; box-to-box involvement across both phases. Reconciles the earlier report language (''run down the right'') with him being the nominal central 10.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(67,6,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Left-back, 4-2-3-1 — subbed 75'' (Digne)','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. High and wide on the left — provided the width/overlap on the flank while Rogers tucked into the left half-space, a complementary LB–inside-forward pairing. Hot zone is the left touchline in the middle-to-attacking third. MOVEMENT: advanced aggressively on Villa''s targeted left side (behind Wan-Bissaka), so his average position sits notably higher than Cash''s. Provided the attacking width so Rogers could drift central. Off at 75'' for Digne.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(68,2,14,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Right-back, 4-2-3-1 — played full 90','(match heatmap analysis)',NULL,'QUALITATIVE READ. More reserved than Maatsen. Supported Villa''s right-sided play behind/around McGinn but sat comparatively deeper, giving a slightly asymmetric fullback picture (Maatsen high-left, Cash a touch more measured on the right) to help screen against Summerville/Diouf and balance the counter. Hot zone: right flank, middle third. MOVEMENT: selective overlaps on the right rather than the sustained high positioning of Maatsen; contributed to the back-three-ish rest defence when Villa built.',NULL,NULL,'rogers-cam-analysis','Medium. Match facts, confirmed XI, formation, substitutions, player roles, the deliberate plan to attack behind Wan-Biss',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(69,9,27,2,8.400000000000000355,88,'Central midfielder — deeper role in the double pivot (''the engine room''), making a late arriving run into the box for his goal','Deep-lying playmaker/tempo-setter who dictated play, then arrived unmarked in the box off a worked short corner. 40/45 accurate passes (89%), 2 key passes, 1 big chance created. Widely a Man-of-the-Match contender.','Central-midfield band near halfway (heaviest), left-half-space channels, one high-value touch cluster in the right-centre of the box for the goal','Hot zones: central midfield around the halfway line and left-of-centre, plus a decisive late spike inside the right-centre of the penalty area for his 41st-minute volley (short corner worked by Digne, crossed by Rogers). Average position: central, slightly deeper than a classic No.10, sitting in front of the defence and progressing the ball vertically. Movement: controlled the tempo from deep, then made a well-timed forward burst into the box to finish — the signature Emery deeper-mid-with-late-runs pattern.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-win-europa-league-as-emery-lifts-his-fifth-title ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only, 2025/26. As a DEEPER central mid / double-pivot (his most frequent Emery role): his season-best club performances came here — Europa League final 8.4 (SofaScore) scoring from a late box ar','02010242215X8414X70001100',39.10000000000000142,46.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(70,9,9,NULL,7.599999999999999645,60,'Central midfielder (deeper distributor role, subbed off ~60'')','Assisted Malen''s opening goal (27'') with a brilliant cross into the box; described as ''majestic in midfield'' and the best player on the pitch for his hour before being withdrawn. Controlled possession and tempo. (Malen took the official Player-of-the-Match with a brace.)','Central-midfield core, right-central channel, one wide-right cluster for the assist delivery','Hot zones: central and right-central midfield, plus wide-right involvement for the assist cross that led to Malen''s header. Average position: central midfield, orchestrating from a controlling deep-to-central band. Movement: dictated the middle of the pitch, drifted right to deliver the assist, high on-ball involvement until his 60th-minute substitution. Note: rating shown is a consolidated estimate — newspaper/outlet ratings ranged from 7.3 (avillafan) to 8/10 (GiveMeSport/aston villa news); the true SofaScore figure sits in the high 7s given the hour played.',0,1,'https://www.givemesport.com/aston-villa-young-boys-europa-league-player-ratings-match-highlights/ ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only, 2025/26. As a DEEPER central mid / double-pivot (his most frequent Emery role): his season-best club performances came here — Europa League final 8.4 (SofaScore) scoring from a late box ar','30232457520X6102541000000',43.10000000000000142,60.10000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(71,9,35,NULL,7.400000000000000355,90,'Central midfielder (deeper central-mid role, played full 90)','Energetic and influential across 90 minutes on his 29th birthday in a dominant semi-final win that sent Villa to the final; fizzed a low shot just wide from 25 yards (34'') and whipped in a dangerous free-kick delivery (19''). Ran the midfield tempo.','Central-midfield core (heaviest), left and right half-spaces, edge-of-box touch for the 34'' shot','Hot zones: central midfield, both half-spaces, with attacking-third touches from set-piece delivery and a shooting effort from range. Average position: central, box-to-box tilt but anchored in the deeper-central band typical of his Emery role. Movement: covered ground energetically, progressed play into the final third, arrived on the edge of the box for his shot. Rating consolidated from FotMob 7.3 and outlet ratings ~7.5.',0,0,'https://onefootball.com/en/news/maatsen-tielemans-and-rogers-get-75-aston-villa-players-rated-in-solid-win-vs-nottingham-forest-40932937 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only, 2025/26. As a DEEPER central mid / double-pivot (his most frequent Emery role): his season-best club performances came here — Europa League final 8.4 (SofaScore) scoring from a late box ar','002013874339X710114213030',48.0,51.29999999999999716);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(72,3,24,1,8.199999999999999289,90,'Right centre-back (RCB) in a 4-2-3-1: Cash–Konsa–Pau Torres–Digne','Right-sided centre-half in Emery''s high-line back four; primary aerial/duel anchor on the right, ball-carrier out from the back, and set-piece threat at the far post. Right CB — right-footed, with left-footed Pau Torres alongside.','Right/central defensive third dominant (def|right 42%, def|centre 28%); moderate central build-up involvement (mid|centre 12%); notable attacking-third right-side presence (att|right 8%, att|centre 4%) from set pieces in a 4-0 rout.','Heat centroid ~x29.0/y34.5 (0-100, y low = right) — RCB slightly narrower than the away leg. Range x2-92: own-half right channel core, with more attacking-third appearances than usual (dominant home tie). 50 heat points, 43 touches, 90 min. Rating corrected to SofaScore official 8.2 (previously 8.3 from news source).',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-rout-bologna-4-0-to-reach-uel-semis ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/15632621/player/827679 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','All three top matches came as RCB. Konsa played RCB essentially every club match in 2025/26. His SofaScore peaks were concentrated in the Europa League knockout run (both his season goals came here);  | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates; rating updated to API value 8.2.','001120001000300003X001563',65.5,29.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(73,3,35,2,7.299999999999999823,90,'Right centre-back (RCB) in a 4-2-3-1, partnering Pau Torres','Right-sided centre-half in a clean-sheet performance that sent Villa to their first European final in 44 years. Dealt firmly with Chris Wood''s physical presence and read Forest''s limited attacking moves well. Right CB.','Split between right defensive third (def|right 35%, def|centre 14%) and central middle third (mid|centre 34%, mid|right 13%) — highest-line, most possession-involved footprint of his three best matches; minimal attacking third (4%).','Heat centroid ~x33.6/y32.1 (0-100, y low = right) — RCB in a high line, stepping constantly into midfield right-centre. Widest involvement of his top-3 (77 heat points, 65 touches, 90 min) in a controlled 4-0 clean-sheet semi. Rating corrected to SofaScore official 7.3 (previously 7.5 from news source).',0,0,'https://www.fotmob.com/players/710159/ezri-konsa ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/15632625/player/827679 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','All three top matches came as RCB. Konsa played RCB essentially every club match in 2025/26. His SofaScore peaks were concentrated in the Europa League knockout run (both his season goals came here);  | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates; rating updated to API value 7.3.','001000000000622002X200122',67.90000000000000569,33.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(74,3,23,3,7.400000000000000355,90,'Right centre-back (RCB), partnering Pau Torres','Right-sided centre-half away from home; opened the scoring with a header and paired the goal with steady distribution, though his overall defensive display drew some criticism (Stan Collymore was unimpressed). Right CB.','Right defensive third dominant (def|right 50%, def|centre 17%); steps into central midfield in build-up (mid|centre 20%, mid|right 9%); rare attacking-third spikes from set pieces (att|centre 2%) — scored the opening header.','Heat centroid ~x28.4/y30.5 on SofaScore 0-100 pitch (y low = right flank) — classic RCB footprint. Activity spans x1-95: anchored in the own right channel, advancing into right-centre midfield in possession, far-post box entries on set pieces. 54 heat points, 48 touches, 90 min.',1,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/bologna-1-3-aston-villa-watkins-brace-konsa-scores ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/15632617/player/827679 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','All three top matches came as RCB. Konsa played RCB essentially every club match in 2025/26. His SofaScore peaks were concentrated in the Europa League knockout run (both his season goals came here);  | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates.','000000000000220001X300032',69.5,28.39999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(75,14,35,1,9.40000000000000035,86,'Central attacking midfielder / No.10','Free No.10 behind Ollie Watkins in a 4-2-3-1; primary creator and penalty taker. Assisted Watkins'' opener by driving into the box, skipping between two defenders to the byline and cutting back; then converted a 58th-minute penalty. 4 key passes, 9 touches in the opposition box, 2 successful dribbles, 8 duels won. Man of the Match / SofaScore highest-rated player on the pitch.','Attacking-third left half-space and centre dominant (att|left 24%, att|centre 18%); heavy left-centre middle third (mid|left 16%, mid|centre 15%); touches in ALL nine zones incl. defensive thirds — a true roaming No.10 with a measured LEFT-of-centre bias.','Heat centroid ~x62.0/y64.3 (0-100, y high = left) — free 10 covering the full pitch width (y5-96) and depth (x7-99). MEASURED NOTE: despite match reports describing right-side drift, the heatmap shows his volume tilted left-of-centre, overlapping Rogers'' left channel. 67 heat points, 53 touches, 4 key passes, 86 min. Rating 9.4 confirmed via SofaScore API.',1,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-4-0-nottingham-forest-buendia-lights-europa-league ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/15632625/player/783126 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Buendía''s very best SofaScore-rated club games in 2025/26 came as a central attacking midfielder (No.10) behind Watkins in the two-legged Europa League run (Forest 9.4, Freiburg final 8.3). During the | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates.','54421X7421233301332022100',35.70000000000000285,62.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(76,14,27,3,8.300000000000000711,81,'Attacking midfielder (central, drifting right)','Scored a ~20-yard strike to double the lead in first-half stoppage time (after a McGinn assist) and provided a defence-splitting assist for Morgan Rogers'' 58th-minute third. 4 key passes; picked up an early yellow card but stayed influential. Player of the Match (Tielemans topped the SofaScore chart at 8.4; Buendía 8.3).','Left half-space middle third overwhelmingly dominant (mid|left 48%); left attacking third (att|left 13%, att|centre 11%) and left defensive cover (def|left 15%) — a LEFT-channel No.10 profile, contradicting the "drifting right" narrative in match reports.','Heat centroid ~x54.0/y72.2 (0-100, y high = left) — operated almost entirely in the left half-space between the lines (y range 26-99, never reached the right flank''s outer lane). MEASURED NOTE: match reports said "drifting right"; SofaScore coordinates show the opposite — his ~20-yard goal and the Rogers assist came from left-centre positions. 54 heat points, 48 touches, 4 key passes, 81 min. Rating 8.3 confirmed via API.',1,1,'https://www.sofascore.com/news/aston-villa-win-europa-league-as-emery-lifts-his-fifth-title ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/15632626/player/783126 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Buendía''s very best SofaScore-rated club games in 2025/26 came as a central attacking midfielder (No.10) behind Watkins in the two-legged Europa League run (Forest 9.4, Freiburg final 8.3). During the | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates. Reported side-of-pitch narrative (right drift) is contradicted by measured coordinates.','3432021130X92004X00030000',27.80000000000000071,54.0);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(77,14,7,2,8.5,71,'Wide-right / hybrid attacking midfielder drifting into the right half-space','Opened the scoring on 28'' with a curled ~20-yard free-kick over the wall; created two big chances, plus defensive contribution (three tackles, five recoveries). Two blocked shots, two key passes, ~67% pass completion from 24 attempts; subbed on 71''. Named Man of the Match. NOTE ON RATING: the 9.0 figure is Sportsdunia''s own player-rating system, not confirmed as the SofaScore number — the SofaScore match page for this fixture did not render for me, so treat 9.0 as an approximate/proxy rating for a clear standout, MOTM display (likely high-8s to ~9 on SofaScore too).','Left attacking third dominant (att|left 31%, att|centre 15%) with left middle third support (mid|left 18%, mid|centre 13%); a distinct right-defensive-third cluster (def|right 13%) from tracking back on the right early on — mixed footprint, but attacking volume clearly LEFT.','Heat centroid ~x54.9/y63.9 (0-100, y high = left) — full-width shift (y4-98, x2-91). MEASURED NOTE: reports labelled him "wide-right/right half-space", but measured attacking volume sits left-of-centre; the right-side work is mostly defensive-third recoveries. Scored a curled free-kick. 55 heat points, 44 touches, 2 key passes, 71 min. Rating corrected to SofaScore official 8.5 (the earlier 9.0 was Sportsdunia''s own scale, flagged as proxy).',1,0,'https://www.sportsdunia.com/football-ratings/aston-villa-vs-bournemouth-player-ratings-premier-league-9th-november-2025 ; heatmap & rating measured via SofaScore API /event/14025014/player/783126 (2026-07-02) ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Buendía''s very best SofaScore-rated club games in 2025/26 came as a central attacking midfielder (No.10) behind Watkins in the two-legged Europa League run (Forest 9.4, Freiburg final 8.3). During the | heat_zones/heat_summary: HIGH — computed directly from SofaScore API heatmap coordinates; rating replaced with SofaScore official 8.5.','24400X8210620103314000107',36.10000000000000142,54.89999999999999858);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(78,7,44,1,7.5,90,'Left centre-back','Left-sided CB in a 4-2-3-1 back four, partnering Ezri Konsa (right CB). Ball-playing, build-up-oriented role: primary left-side progressor and press-resistant distributor while keeping a clean sheet on the road.','Hot zones concentrated in Villa''s LEFT-half defensive third and left half-space, pushing into midfield when Villa had the ball. SofaScore heatmap centroid ~x28.5 (own-half, ~28% up the pitch) / y65 (left-of-centre); his average position (x29.0, y65.5) sat clearly LEFT of partner Konsa (y35.4), with LB Digne/Maatsen wider still (y80-87) — confirming the left-CB read. Movement footprint stretched from deep (x4) up to x89, showing repeated stepping-into-midfield carries (24 ball carries, ~161m) as the left-side build-up outlet rather than a touchline-hugging role.','Dominant, calm, entirely-in-control display and his clear season peak. Perfect distribution: SofaScore logged 88/88 passes (100%) with 95 touches, plus 1 key pass and 1 big chance created (a late headed chance that hit the post). Defensively tidy with 3 clearances, 1 block, 2 recoveries. The Premier League match report independently flagged his 100% passing as the best full-90 100%-accuracy figure in the PL since Aymeric Laporte in Feb 2022 (report cites 85 completed; SofaScore''s tracking logged 88 — minor provider difference, both agree it was flawless).',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/aston-villa-crystal-palace/hP#id:14025058 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only 2025/26, starts with 30+ min (n=21, SofaScore): as LCB ~6.65 avg over 12 apps; as RCB ~6.66 avg over 9 apps — essentially identical either side. His two-best matches came on opposite sides ','0000000000022000X10005100',35.0,28.5);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(79,7,21,2,7.099999999999999645,90,'Right centre-back','Right-sided CB in a 4-2-3-1 back four, partnering Pau Torres (left CB). Progressive, carry-heavy role in a controlled home knockout win — Emery''s own summary was ''controlled rather than spectacular''.','Hot zones in Villa''s RIGHT-of-centre half, extending well into the middle third as Villa dominated. Heatmap centroid ~x37.6 (higher up than the Palace game, reflecting Villa''s control) / y37.1 (right-of-centre); average position (x38.1, y37.6) sat RIGHT of partner Pau Torres (y73.9), with RB Cash tighter to the touchline (y11.5). Movement footprint spanned x3 to x83 — repeated forward carries out of defence into the right half-space rather than deep defending.','Comfortable, front-foot performance managing a first-leg lead. Very progressive on the ball: a team-high-type 43 ball carries covering ~379m, with 59/61 passes completed (97%). Low defensive workload against a passive Lille (1 clearance, 2 recoveries, 1 aerial won, 1 duel won) — the rating reflects composed possession and territory rather than firefighting. Tie-break note: this and the Fenerbahçe match are both exactly 7.1/90 min; ranked #2 here only by recency/slightly higher on-ball volume — treat #2 and #3 as effectively co-equal.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/lille-aston-villa/PsTH#id:15631843 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only 2025/26, starts with 30+ min (n=21, SofaScore): as LCB ~6.65 avg over 12 apps; as RCB ~6.66 avg over 9 apps — essentially identical either side. His two-best matches came on opposite sides ','001100000100660019X100131',62.89999999999999858,37.60000000000000142);
INSERT INTO appearances VALUES(80,7,17,3,7.099999999999999645,90,'Right centre-back','Right-sided CB in a 4-2-3-1 back four, partnering Tyrone Mings (left CB). Deep, defence-first rearguard role protecting a slender away lead — a ''backs-to-the-wall'' night (deputy keeper Bizot made 8 saves).','Hot zones packed into Villa''s RIGHT-side defensive third and central penalty-area edge — a low, compact block. Heatmap centroid ~x27.4 (deep, own third) / y37.8 (right-of-centre); average position (x27.9, y38.2) sat RIGHT of partner Tyrone Mings (y59.9), with RB Cash outside him (y13.7). Movement footprint was the most compressed of the three (spanning to x87 only on rare clearances/outlets), consistent with a defend-the-lead brief and little forward stepping.','Resolute defensive display, stylistically the opposite of the Palace and Lille games. Heavy clearing workload: 10 clearances (his season high in these matches), 4 recoveries, 2 aerials won, 2 duels won. Minimal on-ball involvement by choice — just 38 touches, 21/26 passes, 6 carries (~49m) — as Villa sat deep and soaked pressure. The 7.1 rewards defensive volume and clean-sheet contribution rather than distribution.',0,0,'https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/fenerbahce-aston-villa/Psclb#id:14572701 ; heat_map25 grid from SofaScore API heatmap points (5x5 tool-space, 2026-07-02)','Villa-only 2025/26, starts with 30+ min (n=21, SofaScore): as LCB ~6.65 avg over 12 apps; as RCB ~6.66 avg over 9 apps — essentially identical either side. His two-best matches came on opposite sides ','0100000210002220046100X52',62.20000000000000284,27.39999999999999858);
